description: Weight distribution of any one of the five doubly-even binary [32,16,8] codes (quadratic residue, Reed-Muller, etc.).
references: J. H. Conway and V. S. Pless, On the enumeration of self-dual codes, J. Comb. Theory, A28 (1980), 26-53.
J. H. Conway, V. S. Pless and N. J. A. Sloane, The binary self-dual codes of length up to 32: a revised enumeration, J. Combin. Theory, A 60 (1992), 183-195.
F. J. MacWilliams and N. J. A. Sloane, The Theory of Error-Correcting Codes, Elsevier-North Holland, 1978, p. 443.
links: E. R. Berlekamp and N. J. A. Sloane, Weight Enumerator for Second-Order Reed-Muller Codes, IEEE Trans. Information Theory, IT-16 (1970), 745-751.
N. Heninger, E. M. Rains and N. J. A. Sloane, On the Integrality of n-th Roots of Generating Functions, J. Combinatorial Theory, Series A, 113 (2006), 1732-1745.
M. Terada, J. Asatani and T. Koumoto, Weight Distribution
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
